    Question: Exercise 2: Give an ERD for the following system. 300 employees of a company are organized into d...

    Exercise 2: Give an ERD for the following system. 300 employees of a company are organized into different departments. Each department has a name, a role, and a head (who is also an employee). For each employee, we have his social security number, full name, address, city, country, gender, birthdate, phone, email, and his current department. Note that each employee works for only one department at a time, but he could change from one department to another department. Each time he works for a department, the company signs a contract specifying his salary, start date and end date. Each project in the company could be handled by several departments. For each project, we have a name, start date, end date, a project manager and several employees who work on it. Note that an employee could work on different projects with a specified number of hours. Each employee may have several dependents. For each dependent, we keep track of their name, gender, date of birth and relationship to the employee.
